1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the secrecy performance of a communication system, which is a key topic in information theory. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on the security aspects of two-way relaying, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the optimization of power allocation in a communication system, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves the analysis and optimization of a communication system, which can be viewed as a control system. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although less likely, the paper may also fall under the category of multimedia as it deals with the transmission of information between a base station and a mobile user.
